{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 00:08:51.777913", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- The underlay (RIP-based intra- and inter-router network) is healthy: all relevant prefixes are learned, inter-router links are up, and end-to-end ICMP between internal hosts and external segments works with low RTT and 0% loss.\n- The WireGuard VPN overlay is partially degraded: host_1 can reach the VPN server and web_server_1_2 over the overlay, but cannot reach web_server_1_1 (172.16.1.21). Evidence indicates a missing/incomplete peer configuration for 172.16.1.21 on the VPN hub (vpn_server_1).\n\nKey Observations and Evidence\n1) Underlay routing and reachability\n- FRR routing tables (router1, router2, gateway_router, external_router_1) show correct RIP-learned routes for all 10.0.X.0/24 LANs and 20.0.X.0/24 external LANs; inter-router /31s are present.\n- Representative pings:\n  - host_1 -> host_2: OK (0% loss, ~1.3 ms)\n  - host_1 -> external 20.0.0.2/3/4: OK with low RTTs (1–3 ms)\n- Conclusion: No anomalies detected in the underlay; routing is converged and stable.\n\n2) WireGuard overlay interfaces and listeners\n- host_1:\n  - wg0 up at 172.16.1.11/24; peer endpoint is 20.0.0.2:51820 (vpn_server_1); AllowedIPs: 172.16.1.0/24.\n- vpn_server_1:\n  - UDP 51820 listening.\n  - wg show peers:\n    - host_1 (AllowedIPs 172.16.1.11/32) with recent handshake.\n    - web_server_1_2 (AllowedIPs 172.16.1.22/32).\n    - Notably absent: a peer for 172.16.1.21 (web_server_1_1).\n- web_server_1_1:\n  - wg0 up at 172.16.1.21/24; shows a peer pointing to vpn_server_1 with a handshake reported ~1m24s ago.\n  - Apache is bound only to 172.16.1.21:80 (as intended for “VPN-only” access).\n- web_server_1_2:\n  - wg0 up at 172.16.1.22/24; shows recent handshake to vpn_server_1.\n  - Apache is bound to 172.16.1.22:80 (also VPN-only).\n\n3) Overlay reachability tests (ICMP and HTTP)\n- ICMP from host_1:\n  - 172.16.1.1 (vpn_server_1): OK (0% loss, ~2.4 ms).\n  - 172.16.1.22 (web_server_1_2): OK (0% loss, ~4–6 ms).\n  - 172.16.1.21 (web_server_1_1): FAIL; “From 172.16.1.1 Destination Host Unreachable”.\n    - This indicates packets reach the VPN hub and are rejected there due to no matching peer/route for 172.16.1.21.\n- HTTP service bindings (netstat):\n  - web_server_1_1 listens on 172.16.1.21:80 only.\n  - web_server_1_2 listens on 172.16.1.22:80 only.\n- Curl tests from host_1 to 172.16.1.21/22 returned code 000. Since ICMP to 172.16.1.22 works and the service is listening, this curl anomaly is likely test/tool-related. The inability to reach 172.16.1.21 over ICMP confirms HTTP to 172.16.1.21 will also be inaccessible.\n\nDetected Anomalies\n- VPN overlay path to 172.16.1.21 (web_server_1_1) is broken:\n  - host_1 -> vpn_server_1 (172.16.1.1): OK\n  - host_1 -> web_server_1_2 (172.16.1.22): OK\n  - host_1 -> web_server_1_1 (172.16.1.21): FAIL, with vpn_server_1 emitting ICMP unreachable.\n- vpn_server_1’s wg configuration does not include a peer for web_server_1_1 (172.16.1.21). Conversely, web_server_1_1 reports a handshake to vpn_server_1. This asymmetry suggests a configuration mismatch/inconsistency on vpn_server_1 relative to web_server_1_1.\n\nLocalization of Fault\n- Fault localized to the VPN hub (vpn_server_1) WireGuard configuration:\n  - Missing or incorrect peer/AllowedIPs entry for 172.16.1.21 causes the hub to reject/blackhole traffic to web_server_1_1.\n- Underlay routers and links appear normal; no routing anomalies implicated.\n\nLikely Root Cause\n- vpn_server_1 is missing the WireGuard peer configuration (or correct AllowedIPs mapping) for web_server_1_1 (172.16.1.21). As a result, the hub cannot forward overlay traffic to that node, and returns Destination Host Unreachable when host_1 attempts to reach 172.16.1.21 via the VPN.\n\nImpact\n- web_server_1_1 is inaccessible over the VPN from internal clients (e.g., host_1). Since Apache on web_server_1_1 listens only on 172.16.1.21:80, its web service is effectively unreachable from the internal network.\n- web_server_1_2 is reachable over the VPN and responds to ICMP; HTTP listener is present on 172.16.1.22:80.\n\nAdditional Notes\n- While host_1 can ping 20.0.0.3/.4 (underlay IPs), the web servers are designed to be accessed via their VPN addresses only; their HTTP services are bound only to 172.16.1.x, which aligns with the design.\n- The underlay network is functioning correctly; the issue is confined to the WireGuard overlay control/forwarding configuration on vpn_server_1.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 30237, "output_tokens": 7188, "total_tokens": 37425, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 28928}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 5824}}}
